# Keep the Docker build context small and deterministic. The image only COPYs
# extensions/; excluding caches/artifacts keeps that COPY layer byte-stable (so the
# build cache is reused), and the rest just avoids sending large dirs to the daemon.
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.so
*.egg-info/
**/*.egg-info/
extensions/chamfer_dist/build/
.git/
data/
checkpoints_NeuralUDF/
reconstruction/_denoise_cache/
reconstruction/_smoke_output/
reconstruction/models/*.pth
.claude-memory/
public_repo/
